04680nam a22007935i 9780226485348DE-B159720191022022751.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||191022s2017    ilu    fo  d z      eng d  a97802264853487 a10.7208/97802264853482doi  a(DE-B1597)521339  a(OCoLC)1013182893  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ailucUS-IL 4aBH221.G3bA44 2018 7aARC0000002bisacsh04a701.17223  aLH 611002rvk1 aAlexander, Zeynep Çelik, eauthor.10aKinaesthetic Knowing :bAesthetics, Epistemology, Modern Design /cZeynep Çelik Alexander. 1aChicago : bUniversity of Chicago Press, c[2017] 4c©2017  a1 online resource (336 p.) :b10 color plates, 99 halftones  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIntroduction: A Peculiar Experiment -- t1. Kinaesthetic Knowing: The Nineteenth- Century Biography of Another Kind of Knowledge -- t2. Looking: Wölfflin's Comparative Vision -- t3. Affecting: Endell's Mathematics of Living Feeling -- t4. Drawing: The Debschitz School and Formalism's Subject -- t5. Designing: Discipline and Introspection at the Bauhaus -- tEpilogue -- tAcknowledgments -- tNotes -- tSelected Bibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIs all knowledge the product of thought? Or can the physical interactions of the body with the world produce reliable knowledge? In late-nineteenth-century Europe, scientists, artists, and other intellectuals theorized the latter as a new way of knowing, which Zeynep Çelik Alexander here dubs "kinaesthetic knowing."      In this book, Alexander offers the first major intellectual history of kinaesthetic knowing and its influence on the formation of modern art and architecture and especially modern design education. Focusing in particular on Germany and tracing the story up to the start of World War II, Alexander reveals the tension between intellectual meditation and immediate experience to be at the heart of the modern discourse of aesthetics, playing a major part in the artistic and teaching practices of numerous key figures of the period, including Heinrich Wölfflin, Hermann Obrist, August Endell, László Moholy-Nagy, and many others. Ultimately, she shows, kinaesthetic knowing did not become the foundation of the human sciences, as some of its advocates had hoped, but it did lay the groundwork-at such institutions as the Bauhaus-for modern art and architecture in the twentieth century.     aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aAestheticsxPhysiological aspects. 0aAestheticsxPsychological aspects. 0aAesthetics, Germany19th century. 0aAesthetics, Germany20th century. 0aAesthetics. 0aArtxStudy and teachingzGermany. 0aDesignxPhilosophy. 0aKnowledge, Theory of. 0aPsychology and artzGermany. 0aPsychophysics. 4aImperial Germany. 4aaesthetics. 4aepistemology. 4aexperimental psychology. 4aformalism. 4akinaesthesia. 4akinesthesia. 4amodern design education. 4amodernism. 4apedagogy. 4atechnique. 70(DE-601)1046366100(DE-588)4151276-5aEinfluss2gnd 70(DE-601)1046587110(DE-588)4039827-4aModerne2gnd 70(DE-601)1054521570(DE-588)4163782-3aKinästhesie2gnd 70(DE-601)1058229570(DE-588)4114333-4aKunst2gnd 70(DE-601)1060990860(DE-588)4070914-0aErkenntnistheorie2gnd 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226485348423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226485348.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles